record_data.record_plain_text:
REACTIVE SUPPLY AND VOLTAGE CONTROL FROM GENERATION SOURCES SERVICE
Gibson City Energy Center, LLC (“Seller”) provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service (“Reactive Supply Service”) from the listed facility located in the Ameren Illinois pricing zone in the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc.’s (“MISO”) transmission footprint. This tariff sets forth Seller’s revenue requirement for the provision of Reactive Supply Service from the listed facility pursuant to the Reactive Power Revenue Requirements in Schedule 2 of the MISO’s Open Access Transmission, Energy and Operating Reserve Markets Tariff.
REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
Seller’s revenue requirements for the specified facility shall be calculated as follows:
Gibson City Power Plant Annual Revenue Requirement $1,046,553.12 Monthly Revenue Requirement $87,212.76
